  <updated>2013-12-13T15:45:12Z</updated>
  <author>
    <name>Valera Rozuvan</name>
    <uri>http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku</uri>
    <email>valera.rozuvan@gmail.com</email>
  </author>
  <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;I have often had the need to quickly write some tool/app for demonstration
purposes. It generally consists of an index.html file, some JavaScript files,
and a few CSS files. The bare bones skeleton (template) I wrote from scratch
each and every time, and then added to it the actual content. I always thought
that it would be a good idea to save such a skeleton for future reuse. Finally,
I got around to
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/valera-rozuvan/simple-html5-template&quot;&gt;doing just so&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku/html5/jquery/requirejs/template/simple-html5-template-jquery-requirejs&quot;&gt;Simple HTML5 template with jQuery, and Require JS&lt;/a&gt; was originally published by Valera Rozuvan at &lt;a href=&quot;http://valera-rozuvan.github.io/nintoku&quot;&gt;Nintoku&lt;/a&gt; on December 13, 2013.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
</entry>


